VGrandma Ruby's stepfather Gramps
p39
aVwas one of few black men to retire from Carnegie's mill with his pension.
p40
aVHe worked in high temperatures,
p41
aVtearing down and rebuilding furnaces, cleaning up spilt metal and slag.
p42
aVThe history of a place is written on the body and the landscape.
p43
